comment: Lemma for ~ sylow2a . All the orbits which are not for fixed points have size ` | G | / | G x | ` (where ` G x ` is the stabilizer subgroup) and thus are powers of ` P ` . And since they are all nontrivial (because any orbit which is a singleton is a fixed point), they all divide ` P ` , and so does the sum of all of them. (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 17-Jan-2015.)
